<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Poetry" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Poetry,</orth> 1) the art of a poet: <cit><quote>if music and sweet p. agree,</quote> <bibl n="shak. pp 103" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 103</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>neither savouring of p., wit, nor invention,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 4.2.165" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 2, 165</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) poetical compositions, verse: <cit><quote>like cutler's p.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 5.149" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. V, 149</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the truest p. is the most feigning,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.3.19" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 3, 19</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.3.19" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 3, 19</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.3.19" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 3, 19</bibl> <bibl n="shak. shr 1.1.93" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 1, 93</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 1.2.170" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 170</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.1.134" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 1, 134</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.1.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 1, 14</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>